      • lastIndexOf

        public int lastIndexOf​(T item,
                       int fromIndex)
        Description copied from interface: DSList
        Searches backward from the specified fromIndex of the list for the next occurrence of the specified item and, if found, returns the index where it was found. If not found, then DSList.NOT_FOUND_INDEX is returned. If fromIndex is less than 0, then DSList.NOT_FOUND_INDEX is returned. If fromIndex is greater than or equal to count, then it is silently reduced to (count - 1).
